Have you considered placing these tests in a seperate directory structure to
your normal tests so they can be selected as a group to be run?

Say currently you have:

src/
test/

You then use something like slowtests/, dbtests/ etc.

On Tue, Feb 17, 2009 at 3:54 AM, yme0987654321 &lt;yme0987654321@...&gt;wrote:

&gt;   Hi,
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;ve tried looking around the group but I haven&#39;t seen an answer to
&gt; this. I&#39;m trying to set up a group of tests that runs only under
&gt; certain circumstances. Because they are database tests, they have
&gt; expensive setup and teardown procedures (via DBUnit), so they are
&gt; segregated to run separately. The way to get that done seems to be via
&gt; a separate runner, so I hacked up a class that looks like this:
&gt; (Inspiration from here:
&gt; http://schuchert.wikispaces.com/CustomJunit4RunnerJUnit4_4 but that
&gt; example no longer applies to the 4.5 API):
&gt;
&gt; public class SlowTestRunner extends Runner {
&gt;
&gt; private Runner runner;
&gt; private Class&lt;?&gt; klass;
&gt;
&gt; public SlowTestRunner(Class&lt;?&gt; klass, RunnerBuilder builder)
&gt; throws Throwable {
&gt; this.klass = klass;
&gt; if (Boolean.getBoolean(&quot;RunSlowTests&quot;)) {
&gt; runner = getAppropriateRunner(builder);
&gt; } else {
&gt; runner = new IgnoredClassRunner(klass);
&gt; }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; private Runner getAppropriateRunner(RunnerBuilder builder) {
&gt; List&lt;RunnerBuilder&gt; builders = Arrays.asList(
&gt; new IgnoredBuilder(),
&gt; new AnnotatedBuilder(builder),
&gt; new SuiteMethodBuilder(),
&gt; new JUnit3Builder(),
&gt; new JUnit4Builder());
&gt;
&gt; for (RunnerBuilder each : builders) {
&gt; Runner runner = each.safeRunnerForClass(klass);
&gt; if (runner != null && runner.getClass() != this.getClass())
&gt; return runner;
&gt; }
&gt; //this is actually never going to happen, at least in the
&gt; current implementation because the JUnit4Builder is the Builder of
&gt; last resort.
&gt; return new ErrorReportingRunner(klass, new
&gt; InitializationError(&quot;Unable to find suitable runner to delegate for &quot;
&gt; + klass.getName()));
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; public Description getDescription() {
&gt; return runner.getDescription();
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; public void run(RunNotifier notifier) {
&gt; runner.run(notifier);
&gt; }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; The method getAppropriateRunner is basically a copy/paste from
&gt; AllDefaultPossibilitiesBuilder. I had to copy paste because the
&gt; protected method forced a return of an AnnotatedBuilder, instead of
&gt; just a RunnerBuilder, so overriding wasn&#39;t working well. Note the case
&gt; here is that I&#39;m not sure if the class is a JUnit3 or 4 class, and I
&gt; want to support both with one runner.
&gt;
&gt; At first I tried to just do a runnerForClass on builder passed to the
&gt; constructor, but that causes an infinite loop, because the class has
&gt; the RunWith annotation on it that references the very same Runner.
&gt;
&gt; Am I correct that the API isn&#39;t naturally supporting what I am trying
&gt; to do, or is there another way to accomplish this?
&gt;
&gt;  
&gt;



